What is the difference between navigation and tab controllers? Under what circumstances do you use each one?\
\pard\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\pardirnatural\qr\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf0 >> The navigation controller is where different view controllers are connected through a segue that can be moved between by a button that the user taps to move to a new view and a back button the user taps to move back to a previous view. It would serve an application the best in the case of an order of views being important because it takes you from one to the next to the next. The tab controller consists of a bar that contains different tabs with icons that the user can choose from in order to take him/her to a different view. The tab controller would be the best option when the order of the views doesn\'92t matter, and rather the choice of the user to see all options at once is more important.
